            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "There was trouble for Daytona Bike Week for many years, and it hit a boiling point in 1986. Local residents called it an “invasion” while law enforcement clashed with some riders. That’s when the city and local chamber of commerce worked to help change the nature of the gathering. Things have changed considerably since then, with Bike Week lasting 10 days and hundreds of events being held all over Volusia County.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
